From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 12 Jul 2026 20:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add the GRX-014 cluster_store recording-smoke and gated

 real-pass opt-in arms with result writeback scaffold

Stacked on 0001..0024. This is the GRX-014 bridge-recording / real-pass
opt-in slice (the GRX-009 0008+0009+0010 layers merged into one patch for
the cluster_store pass), mirroring GRX-013 0022. It is a bring-up gate, not
a default enablement, and it does not change the shipping fallback semantics.
Authored under the GRX Wave 4 print-gating discipline: every per-dispatch
stdout marker below is harness instrumentation gated under the harness-only
dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in, so the production dispatch_real_pass opt-in
path emits zero per-dispatch stdout (pass engagement is read from the shim
engagement counter file / RXGD_SUMMARY instead).

- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: adds three per-pass opt-in
  settings that all default to false and are separate from
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/enabled:
  .../cluster_store/dispatch_recording_smoke,
  .../cluster_store/dispatch_real_pass, and
  .../cluster_store/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h: declares the reserved cluster_store
  real-pass arm flag RXGD_CAP_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS (bridge value 1 << 8)
  carried in RxGdCaps.flags. This reuses the existing flags field: the C
  ABI struct layout and RXGD_ABI_VERSION are unchanged.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp: try_create_session() sets
  RXGD_CAP_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS ONLY when the cluster_store
  dispatch_real_pass opt-in is enabled, and clears RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64 ONLY
  when the harness-only cluster_store real_pass_force_capability_downgrade knob
  is enabled (cluster_store's kernel carries no i64 push-constant fields, so
  int64 is not part of its binding preflight, but the bridge's dispatch
  eligibility requires it for the recording harness).
  try_record_cluster_store() emits RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS
  and RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_CLUSTER_STORE_RECORD only on the real-pass arm OK
  path; both markers are gated under the harness-only
  dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in.
- cluster_builder_rd.cpp bake_cluster store segment: when
  try_record_cluster_store() returned true on the real-pass arm, the bridge
  dispatched the cluster_store merge kernel into the real cluster_buffer
  destination ID3D12Resource*, so the packed cluster table result is
  physically written into the destination buffer. The result writeback
  SCAFFOLD prints RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK (under
  the recording-smoke opt-in), then clears the flag so the FULL native Godot
  cluster store dispatch still runs as the continuation/backstop (GPU math
  parity is still pending in-engine observation; the native dispatch re-packs
  the whole table from the same raster-segment input, so the rendered image
  can never change while the scaffold is in place).

The bridge fails closed on the real-pass arm and returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK
with a machine-readable RXGD_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic naming
the FIRST missing prerequisite; the real dispatch is only linked under the
test-only d3d12-recording-shim bridge feature. This does not change
RXGD_ABI_VERSION, does not enable the pass by default (all four cluster_store
per-pass settings still default to false), does not flip real_gpu_pass to
true by itself, and makes no visual, measured-telemetry, GPU-timestamp, or
performance claim by itself.
---
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
index 3f5bdf9..6c6d0b3 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
@@ -208,6 +208,41 @@ void initialize_rurix_accel_module(ModuleInitializationLevel p_level) {
 	// RXGD_PASS_CLUSTER_STORE, so the native cluster store keeps rendering
 	// in practice and no acceleration is claimed.
 	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/enabled", false);
+	// GRX-014: harness-only Godot-runtime cluster_store bridge dispatch
+	// recording smoke opt-in (0008-level). Defaults to false so the
+	// shipping build never arms the recording-smoke marker path. It gates
+	// the module-side RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_CLUSTER_STORE_RECORD marker AND
+	// (GRX Wave 4 print gating) the per-dispatch REAL_PASS / WRITEBACK
+	// instrumentation markers; the bridge record path itself is only linked
+	// when the loaded rurix_godot.dll is built with the test-only
+	// d3d12-recording-shim feature AND the dispatch_real_pass opt-in below
+	// armed the fail-closed real-pass gate.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/dispatch_recording_smoke", false);
+	// GRX-014: opt-in gated REAL cluster_store pass bring-up arm (0009-level).
+	// Defaults to false so the shipping build never arms the real-pass
+	// attempt. Even when enabled the bridge runs its runtime binding
+	// preflight, dispatch eligibility, per-slot kernel-binding-kind
+	// conformance (structured_buffer/structured_buffer/rwstructured_buffer),
+	// and math-parity checks and keeps returning RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK (with a
+	// machine-readable RXGD_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic naming
+	// the first missing prerequisite) unless every check passes AND a
+	// runtime-mappable real dispatch path is linked (d3d12-recording-shim
+	// builds only); the shipping feature-off bridge fails closed with
+	// real_dispatch_path_not_linked, so the native cluster store keeps
+	// rendering.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/dispatch_real_pass", false);
+	// GRX-014: harness-only forced-failure knob for the cluster_store fallback
+	// red/green leg (0009-level template of the luminance
+	// real_pass_force_capability_downgrade). When enabled the module clears the
+	// shader-int64 capability it advertises to the bridge. cluster_store carries
+	// no i64 push-constant fields, so (like particles_copy and unlike the
+	// texture passes) int64 is not part of its binding preflight; the bridge's
+	// cluster_store dispatch eligibility still requires the int64 device
+	// capability for the recording harness, so clearing it fails the real-pass
+	// arm closed with unsupported_device while the native Godot cluster store
+	// path keeps rendering. Defaults to false; never enabled by the shipping
+	// build/config.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade", false);
 
 #if defined(D3D12_ENABLED)
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/enabled")) {
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
index c146e60..1346ff9 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
@@ -287,6 +287,25 @@ void RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_create_session() {
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/particles_copy/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade")) {
 		caps.flags &= ~RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64;
 	}
+	// GRX-014: arm the opt-in gated REAL cluster_store pass attempt ONLY when
+	// the default-false cluster_store dispatch_real_pass opt-in is enabled. The
+	// bridge still fails closed (fallback + RXGD_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED
+	// first missing prerequisite) unless every gate passes AND the
+	// d3d12-recording-shim real dispatch path is linked and completes; this
+	// is a bring-up gate, not a default runtime pass.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/dispatch_real_pass")) {
+		caps.flags |= RXGD_CAP_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS;
+	}
+	// GRX-014: harness-only cluster_store forced-failure knob. cluster_store
+	// carries no i64 push-constant fields so int64 is not part of its binding
+	// preflight, but the bridge's cluster_store dispatch eligibility still
+	// requires the int64 device capability for the recording harness; clearing it
+	// makes the real-pass arm fail closed with unsupported_device while the
+	// native Godot cluster store path keeps rendering. The fallback red/green leg
+	// of the GRX-014 real-pass enablement smoke verifies exactly this.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade")) {
+		caps.flags &= ~RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64;
+	}
 	if (adapter_luid_valid) {
 		memcpy(caps.adapter_luid, &adapter_luid, sizeof(adapter_luid));
 	}
@@ -893,6 +912,22 @@ bool RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_record_cluster_store(uint64_t p_cluster_render_na
 		}
 		return false;
 	}
+	// GRX-014: only reachable when the bridge's opt-in real-pass arm actually
+	// returned RXGD_STATUS_OK after a real recorded dispatch (d3d12-recording-
+	// shim builds only; the shipping feature-off bridge always falls back with
+	// real_dispatch_path_not_linked first). GRX Wave 4 print gating: both
+	// per-dispatch stdout markers are harness instrumentation and are gated
+	// under the harness-only dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in — the production
+	// dispatch_real_pass path emits zero per-dispatch stdout (pass engagement
+	// is read from the shim engagement counter file / RXGD_SUMMARY instead).
+	// The REAL_PASS marker reports the real-pass arm; the RECORD marker is the
+	// recording-smoke marker.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS: pass=RXGD_PASS_CLUSTER_STORE dispatched=1");
+	}
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_CLUSTER_STORE_RECORD: pass=RXGD_PASS_CLUSTER_STORE recorded=1");
+	}
 	return true;
 }
 
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
index 8590d2d..8843502 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
@@ -78,6 +78,17 @@
 // an RXGD_PARTICLES_COPY_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic unless every check passes
 // AND the d3d12-recording-shim real dispatch path is linked and completes.
 #define RXGD_CAP_PARTICLES_COPY_REAL_PASS 128u
+// GRX-014 opt-in cluster_store real-pass arm carried in RxGdCaps.flags (ABI
+// v1, no struct layout change; bridge value 1 << 8). Set only when the
+// default-false rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/dispatch_real_pass
+// opt-in is enabled. Setting it never on its own makes the bridge return
+// RXGD_STATUS_OK: the fail-closed ClusterStoreGate runs preflight ->
+// eligibility -> binding-kind (structured_buffer/structured_buffer/
+// rwstructured_buffer) -> math-parity -> linked-dispatch checks and returns
+// RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK with an RXGD_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED
+// diagnostic unless every check passes AND the d3d12-recording-shim real
+// dispatch path is linked and completes.
+#define RXGD_CAP_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS 256u
 
 typedef struct RxGdCaps {
 	uint32_t abi_version;
diff --git a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/cluster_builder_rd.cpp b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/cluster_builder_rd.cpp
index 09dc94a..355f814 100644
--- a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/cluster_builder_rd.cpp
+++ b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/cluster_builder_rd.cpp
@@ -34,6 +34,9 @@
 #include "servers/rendering/rendering_server_globals.h" // IWYU pragma: keep. RENDER_TIMESTAMP macro uses RSG.
 
 // GRX-014 segment: opt-in cluster_store gate lives on the D3D12 hooks.
+// GRX Wave 4 print gating: GLOBAL_GET gates the harness-only per-dispatch
+// writeback marker below.
+#include "core/config/project_settings.h"
 #include "drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h"
 
 ClusterBuilderSharedDataRD::ClusterBuilderSharedDataRD() {
@@ -569,6 +572,29 @@ void ClusterBuilderRD::bake_cluster() {
 					// RenderElementData (80 bytes) x render_element_max.
 					const uint32_t rurix_render_elements_bytes = (uint32_t)(sizeof(RenderElementData) * render_element_max);
 					rurix_recorded_cluster_store = D3D12Hooks::get_singleton()->try_record_cluster_store(rurix_cluster_render_handle, rurix_render_elements_handle, rurix_cluster_store_handle, cluster_render_buffer_size, rurix_render_elements_bytes, cluster_buffer_size, (const uint8_t *)&push_constant, (uint32_t)sizeof(ClusterBuilderSharedDataRD::ClusterStore::PushConstant));
+					if (rurix_recorded_cluster_store) {
+						// GRX-014 result writeback SCAFFOLD (0010-level). The Rurix
+						// bridge dispatched the cluster_store merge kernel into the
+						// real cluster_buffer destination ID3D12Resource*, so the
+						// packed cluster table result is physically written into the
+						// destination buffer. Record that writeback with a machine-
+						// readable marker, then keep the FULL native Godot cluster
+						// store dispatch as the continuation/backstop: GPU math
+						// parity is still pending measurement (the kernel math is
+						// CPU-proven integer-exact, but the in-engine result has not
+						// been observed), the shim submit executes outside Godot's
+						// frame command order, and the native dispatch re-packs the
+						// whole table from the same raster-segment input, so the
+						// rendered image can never change while this scaffold is in
+						// place.
+						// GRX Wave 4 print gating: harness instrumentation only
+						// (dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in); zero per-dispatch
+						// stdout on the production path.
+						if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+							print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK: dst=cluster_buffer native_continuation=active scaffold=1");
+						}
+						rurix_recorded_cluster_store = false;
+					}
 				}
 			}
 #endif
